    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="393"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1311.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi> I have the honor to inform you that immediately
                    upon the receipt this morning of your telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d393fn1"
                        >Printed, <ref target="#pg_313">p. 313</ref>.</note> announcing the receipt,
                    through the governor of Shantung and Chinese minister in Washington, of a cipher
                    message from Minister Conger in Pekin, I called at the foreign office and
                    communicated its contents to Mr. von Derenthall, Count von Bülow being
                    indisposed. His reply was substantially as contained in my telegram to you of
                    to-day’s date, which I have the honor to confirm (paraphrase): <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>(Finding information from China so contradictory and unsatisfactory,
                            minister of foreign affairs has little hope of securing anything
                            definite or trustworthy at present, but will continue to endeavor to do
                            so, and will immediately inform the United States in case of
                            success.)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">And. D. White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
